<a name="top"></a>
Transaction feedback allows members to give feedback
on a transaction, for instance on the quality of the delivered service. It helps
to get an impression of member's quality and reliability. The buyer can give
feedback to the seller, and the seller can give one reply to the buyer.
Transaction feedback can be enabled and disabled by the administration.<br>
Besides Transaction feedback cyclos also knows the <a
	href="${pagePrefix}references"><u>reference</u></a> system, which functions
independently of it. In references qualification takes place on a member level;
in transaction feedback it takes place on transaction level.

<span class="member">
<i>Waar te vinden</i><br> 
When enabled, you find Transaction feedback under &quot;Menu: Personal > Feedback
transactions&quot;.</span>

<span class="admin">
<i>How to get it working.</i><br>
To enable or disable Transaction feedback, go to &quot;Menu: accounts > Manage accounts > Edit icon > Transaction types >
edit icon&quot; and set the <a href="${pagePrefix}account_management#transaction_type_details"><u>
appropriate values</u></a>.</span> 
<hr>

<a name="feedbacks_summary"></a>
<h3>Transaction feedbacks</h3>
This is an overview of received and given <a href="#top"><u>feedbacks</u></a> .
<br><br>
If you select the radio button &quot;Received feedbacks&quot;, you see the
number of feedbacks received in all available values, both over the last 30
days, and over the total time as a member.
<br><br>
At the bottom of the list you see the total number of feedbacks and the
percentage of the feedbacks that was positive, also over the last 30 days and
the total membership period.
<br><br>
If you select the radio button &quot;Given feedbacks&quot;, you see the number
of feedbacks given in every available value, also over the last 30 days and 
over the full time span.
<br><br>
To view payments awaiting feedback, click &quot;View payments awaiting
feedback&quot;.
<hr class="help">

